Package: fastlowess
Title: Rust-Based LOWESS Smoothing
Version: 0.99.0
Authors@R: person("Amir", "Valizadeh", email = "thisisamirv@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides high-performance LOWESS smoothing (Locally Weighted Scatterplot Smoothing) 
    using a Rust backend. Supports various weight functions, robustness iterations, 
    streaming/online processing, cross-validation, and uncertainty quantification.
    Applicable to genomic data, time series, and general-purpose smoothing tasks.
License: MIT + file LICENSE-MIT | Apache License 2.0 + file LICENSE-APACHE
SystemRequirements: Cargo (Rust's package manager), rustc (only required when installing from source)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
biocViews: Preprocessing, Smoothing, StatisticalMethod, Regression
Suggests: BiocStyle, knitr, rmarkdown, testthat (>= 3.0.0)
VignetteBuilder: knitr
